==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neoplatonism
<hw>Ne`o*pla"to*nism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Neo-</ets> + <ets>Platonism</ets>.]</ety> <def>A pantheistic
eclectic school of philosophy, of which <persfn>Plotinus</persfn> was
the chief (<sc>a. d.</sc> 205-270), and which sought to reconcile the
Platonic and Aristotelian systems with Oriental theosophy. It tended to
mysticism and theurgy, and was the last product of Greek
philosophy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neoplatonist</ent>⟦br⟧
